==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scissorstail
<hw>Scis"sors*tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A tyrant flycatcher (<spn>Milvulus forficatus</spn>) of the
Southern United States and Mexico, which has a deeply forked tail. It is
light gray above, white beneath, salmon on the flanks, and fiery red at
the base of the crown feathers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scissors-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
